					.accordion__content 
						p Anthropologists would study different types of society during the colonial and industrial periods and note the differences between ‘Europeans’ and the others, but this distinction between our formerly incredibly diverse cultures and the European/American world-system is increasingly disappearing. Heterogeneity is disappearing and homogeneity is the rule, we will think the same, talk the same, act the same and believe the same. Our objectives will be united in global conformity.
